snippet.title: How to Dance the Armenian Kochari
snippet.description:
June 2012 - COAF presents: Volodya and Zhenya, along with the Sasun Dance Group from the village of Lernagog, teach you how to dance one version of the Armenian Kochari dance. 

The Sasun Dance Group is just one of the many initiatives that COAF has implemented to help enrich children in the villages of the Armavir Region with extracurricular activities, sports, and the arts. COAF aims to provide students with opportunities to experience alternative ways of learning and to develop personal interests and talents in an informal environment. We also recognize the importance of sports and the arts and seek to enrich students outside of traditional academics whenever possible.

To read a blog post about the making of this video click here: http://coafkids.org/blog/how-to-save-a-generation-dance/

Written by Lily Abagyan and Hayk Hovsepyan (MenkMedia.com)
Produced by Lily Abagyan, Hayk Hovsepyan, and Children of Armenia Fund
Cinematography by Lily Abagyan
Edited by Hayk Hovsepyan
Kochari related expertise provided by Gagik Ginosyan
Special thanks to the COAF team, Mrs. Kamalyan, Gagik Ginosyan

snippet.title: How to Greek Dance: Hasapiko
snippet.description:
To learn more Greek dancing, visit http://www.krikoslearning.com. Sign up to receive a FREE music playlist to practice the Hasapiko to.

I'm going to show you how to dance the basic steps of the Hasapiko.

Want to dance at an upcoming wedding or baptism... but you're just not sure how? Can't find time for lessons at your local church? Greek dancing is a skill that can be learned. You can pick it up quickly and easily, and gain confidence while doing it. Visit http://www.krikoslearning.com.

-----
Background: With roots in the years of the Byzantine Empire, the 'hasapiko' (χασάπικο) has become perhaps the most famous Greek dance to non-Greeks since it was choreographed as the 'sirtaki' (συρτάκι) for Anthony Quinn in the 1964 film 'Zorba the Greek'. It is sometimes also called the "sailors' dance."
